subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen of male.
Terga and sterna II–VIII darkening from yellow to brown; terga II– VIII each with a narrow black antecosta; tergum VIII deeply emarginate in a V-shape along posterior margin (
Figure 5C
). Epandrial lobes pale brown, slightly shorter than gonocoxite (
Figure 5A
), with some short black setae on median portion of inner side and near median portion of ventral margin (
Figure 5D
), and a row of blackish brown long setae subapically on the ventral margin (
Figure 5C, D
). Tergum X saddle-like, extending around the base of cerci to lateral side (
Figure 5A, B
). Upper branch of proctiger protruding from between the two epandrial lobes, strongly sclerotized laterally, slightly curved cephalad apically, with a bundle of long yellow setae at the posterior region of apex. Lower branch of proctiger elongate, with slender setae along margin, tapering toward apex (
Figure 5A, B
). Cercus subacute at apex, corresponding to half length of gonocoxite (
Figures 4
, 
5A
). Gonocoxite hemispherical, consisting of two halves, which are fused basally and separated by a V-shaped membranous area caudally (
Figure 5E
). Gonostylus short, bearing long setae, stout basally and pointed apically, with a glabrous sclerotized process medially (
Figure 5E
). Aedeagus broad basally, with a pair of short truncated aedeagal lobes (
Figure 5E
). Penisfilum long and coiled (
Figure 5A
).

Abdomen of female.
Coloration of terga and sterna similar to male. Terga II–VI each with a narrow black antecosta on anterior margins; terga VII and IX each with a short and narrow antecosta, and tergum VIII with a long and broad antecosta, emarginate on posterior margin (
Figure 6C
); two lateral corners each connected to a dark brown sclerite whose ventral margin deeply emarginate in a V-shape (
Figure 6A
). A pointed dorsal process of subgenital plate extending into the emargination (
Figure 6A, B
); the subgenital plate irregular in shape, with two membranous emarginations along the lateral margin, and divided by a broad triangular membranous area into two halves, each of which bears a bundle of black setae at distal end; a spiracle in the front emargination (
Figure 6A, B
). Tergum X extremely narrow, usually extending ventrally (
Figure 6A
), but not extending ventrally in specimens collected from Fanjingshan. Anal plates yellowish brown and rounded apically, roughly as long as cerci (
Figure 6A, C, D
). Spermatheca swollen, constricted roughly at the middle (
Figure 6E
).
